  "text": "Moreover, the persistence of parasite antigens in the dendritic and cardiac cells [CITATION_1] 48] , the occurrence of antiidiotypic antibodies mimicrying parasite epitopes, and the presence of anti-laminin and anti-carbohydrate epitopes antibodies as well as cross-reactivity with other microorganisms such as intestinal or lung bacterias/protozoa may count for the long-term persistence of residual conventional serology after effective treatment of Chagas disease host [CITATION_2] . Taking into account all these factors, an important question may arise: \"is it really necessary to consider the negativation of the conventional serology as the only way for discrimination between cured and not cured patients?\"",
